This is the Energy Analysis portion of the Macroeconomic Analysis project. 
Although it was initially aptly named, holding only petroleum trade data, it
is now a misnomer because this Energy Analysis has been expanded to include the
Commodity Futures Trading Commission's Commitment of Traders Reports 
(aggregated options and futures) on non-petroleum products as well. The folder
names are self-descriptive enough to understand, and each follows the same 
structure. For each cftc_cot_... folder, there is (1) an initialization file,
(2) a historical webscraping file, (3) a new data collection file, and (4) a
file to call data that has been collected (however, 4 is limited as it is
currently set for petroleum products so the inputs need to be updated in the
respective get_data_... .R files in each cftc_cot folder). It also includes 
scripts to collect weekly Energy Information Association data (EIA) data
on storage quantities and aggregated balance sheets. Also included is a mapping
folder. This folder is just a rough geographic map of pipelines and refineries.

It is recommended that once you download the historical files, that you either
run the new_data file for each commodity group after each CFTC COT release and
EIA release or that you write a script to schedule these events. If you don't
the next run of the new data file will only collect the most recent date, 
retaining that missed spot.